  "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0003": {
    "node_id": "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0003",
    "parent_id": "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0001",
    "level": 2,
    "node_kind": "heading",
    "heading_text": "Multiple body parameters",
    "anchor_id": "multiple-body-parameters",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-multiple-params/#multiple-body-parameters",
    "section_text": "In the previous example, the path operations would expect a JSON body with the attributes of an Item , like:\n\nBut you can also declare multiple body parameters, e.g. item and user :\n\nIn this case, FastAPI will notice that there is more than one body parameter in the function (there are two parameters that are Pydantic models).\n\nSo, it will then use the parameter names as keys (field names) in the body, and expect a body like:\n\nFastAPI will do the automatic conversion from the request, so that the parameter item receives its specific content and the same for user .\n\nIt will perform the validation of the compound data, and will document it like that for the OpenAPI schema and automatic docs.",
    "section_inline_code": [
      "Item",
      "item",
      "user"
    ],
    "section_links": [],
    "code_refs": [
      {
        "type": "code_ref",
        "path": "../../docs_src/body_multiple_params/tutorial002_py310.py",
        "highlight_lines": [
          20
        ],
        "raw": "{* ../../docs_src/body_multiple_params/tutorial002_py310.py hl[20] *}",
        "section_id": "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0003",
        "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-multiple-params/#multiple-body-parameters"
      }
    ],
    "code_blocks": [
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "language": "JSON",
        "text": "{\n    \"name\": \"Foo\",\n    \"description\": \"The pretender\",\n    \"price\": 42.0,\n    \"tax\": 3.2\n}",
        "section_id": "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0003",
        "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-multiple-params/#multiple-body-parameters"
      },
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "language": "JSON",
        "text": "{\n    \"item\": {\n        \"name\": \"Foo\",\n        \"description\": \"The pretender\",\n        \"price\": 42.0,\n        \"tax\": 3.2\n    },\n    \"user\": {\n        \"username\": \"dave\",\n        \"full_name\": \"Dave Grohl\"\n    }\n}",
        "section_id": "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0003",
        "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-multiple-params/#multiple-body-parameters"
      }
    ]
  },
  "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0004": {
    "node_id": "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0004",
    "parent_id": "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0001",
    "level": 2,
    "node_kind": "heading",
    "heading_text": "Singular values in body",
    "anchor_id": "singular-values-in-body",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-multiple-params/#singular-values-in-body",
    "section_text": "The same way there is a Query and Path to define extra data for query and path parameters, FastAPI provides an equivalent Body .\n\nFor example, extending the previous model, you could decide that you want to have another key importance in the same body, besides the item and user .\n\nIf you declare it as is, because it is a singular value, FastAPI will assume that it is a query parameter.\n\nBut you can instruct FastAPI to treat it as another body key using Body :\n\nIn this case, FastAPI will expect a body like:\n\nAgain, it will convert the data types, validate, document, etc.",
    "section_inline_code": [
      "Query",
      "Path",
      "Body",
      "importance",
      "item",
      "user"
    ],
    "section_links": [],
    "code_refs": [
      {
        "type": "code_ref",
        "path": "../../docs_src/body_multiple_params/tutorial003_an_py310.py",
        "highlight_lines": [
          23
        ],
        "raw": "{* ../../docs_src/body_multiple_params/tutorial003_an_py310.py hl[23] *}",
        "section_id": "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0004",
        "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-multiple-params/#singular-values-in-body"
      }
    ],
    "code_blocks": [
      {
        "type": "code_block",
        "language": "JSON",
        "text": "{\n    \"item\": {\n        \"name\": \"Foo\",\n        \"description\": \"The pretender\",\n        \"price\": 42.0,\n        \"tax\": 3.2\n    },\n    \"user\": {\n        \"username\": \"dave\",\n        \"full_name\": \"Dave Grohl\"\n    },\n    \"importance\": 5\n}",
        "section_id": "tutorial/body-multiple-params::section-0004",
        "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/body-multiple-params/#singular-values-in-body"
      }
    ]
  },
